From: Performance Patch Series
Subject: [PATCH 08/10] Parallelize GetObjects metadata fetching

Bottleneck #6: The GetCatalogs→GetDbSchemas→GetTableSchemas chain
processes each catalog, dataset, and table sequentially. For a project
with many datasets or tables, this means each INFORMATION_SCHEMA query
waits for the previous one to complete.

This patch parallelizes:
1. GetDbSchemas: Fetches schemas for all matching catalogs in parallel
2. GetTableSchemas: Fetches column/constraint metadata for all tables
   within a dataset in parallel

The outer GetCatalogs loop stays sequential (listing projects is one
API call), but the inner dataset-level and table-level work fans out
using Task.WhenAll.

Thread safety: Each parallel task uses its own builders and only writes
to a ConcurrentBag. Results are merged back in sorted order at the end.

